SocketsHpp is a header-only library. No linking is required.

To use SocketsHpp in your CMake project:

    find_package(SocketsHpp CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE SocketsHpp::SocketsHpp)

Or simply include the headers:

    #include <sockets.hpp>
    #include <SocketsHpp/http/server/http_server.h>

Dependencies (automatically handled by vcpkg):
- nlohmann-json
- cpp-jwt  
- bshoshany-thread-pool
